children: Vancouver Crime Analysis
Visualizations are created to answer the questions below:
a) What are the major problems each neighbourhood is facing
b) Where did the crimes occur on a given day

c) Where does each type of major crimes tend to occur

d) How does each type of crime change over time
Solution - Network Graph
a) What are the major problems each neighbourhood is facing

- Outer grey nodes: Neighbourhoods
- Node size: total # of crimes


- Inner nodes: types of crimes
- Similar crime types are grouped into the same color (e.g. theft, break and enter) 


- Edge width & color gradient: proportion of each type of crime in that neighbourhood
(e.g. the most obvious one is the Sunset community, where theft of vehicles outweighs any other types of cirmes in that region)

c) Where do each type of crime
tend to occur?
If we have tons of data, we can conduct analysis on each individual category
Then, we can reduce the opacity of each data point on the map plot, and the region with darker color means more data points overlap here, and therefore more crime instaces occured here
Theft of Vehicle
Clearly, Downtown area, Commerical Broadway and SE Marine Drive are of major concerns
Vehicle Collision
Vehicle collision tend to occur in Downarea, Broadway, Hastings and Marine drive
Commercial Break-in
Commercial break-ins are more likely to occur in business areas, such as Downtown, Broadway, 4th Ave, Kingsway, and Hastings
Residential Break-in
Unlike the above cases, there is no clear pattern for residential break-in... it can occur randomly in any place
